AGI - Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a law that lowers the age of military service from 27 to 25 years. The law, adopted a year ago by Members and waiting to be promulgated by the Presidency, will enter into force tomorrow, said Rada, the Ukrainian parliament, on its website. The Ukrainian Government will then have to adapt the various regulatory texts to the new age of mobilization within six months. The army was debated in&nbsp; Ukraine&nbsp; for months. The Ukrainian army suffered losses, whose entity is kept secret, and today, unlike the beginning of the conflict, struggles to find volunteers for the front.&nbsp;
<br> In February, the Rada approved a series of measures to facilitate mobilization, after a first draft prepared by the government had been postponed to be rewritten a few weeks earlier. In December 2023, Volodymyr Zelensky claimed that the army had offered to mobilize up to 500,000 more people, number then revised to the downfall by the new commander-in-chief of the Ukrainian army, Oleksandre Syrsky. The current recruitment system is considered by many unjust, inefficient and often corrupt Ukrainians. It is also called for the demobilization of those who have long been in the front.
<br And speaking of war, from the beginning of the year more than 400 square kilometers of territory in the Ukrainian "new regions" that Russia annexed have passed under the control of the Russian armed forces and five settlements were released in March. The Russian Defence Minister Serghei Shoigu said this, according to Ria Novosti. "Thanks to the courage and professionalism of our military personnel, in the last month in the People's Republic of Donetsk were released the settlements of Nevelskoye, Orlovka, Tonenkoye, Krasnoye and the village of Mirnoye in the Zaporozhye region. In total, from the beginning of the year, 403 square kilometers of the territory of new regions of the Russian Federation have passed under our control", said in a thematic teleconference with the leadership of the armed forces of the Russian Federation.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

